  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig node\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nI upgraded my cluster from 1.7 -> 1.8.1 and realized that all my failure domain & region labels were gone. \r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nI expect those labels to remain\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nWithout a cloud provider (bare metal) or with the CCM, restart a 1.8.x kubelet and you'll see that the node is updated w/o the zone labels. \r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nThe offending commit that caused this issue is [here](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/commit/80156474cf46b919b5d4b51a4676dc395c3e90dc#diff-6b0808bd1afb15f9f77986f4459601c2). The external cloud providers will also be impacted by this since the labels will be removed; however, since the cloud taint is gone they will never attempt to add those labels back. \r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8.x\r\n\r\ncc @mrIncompetent @wlan0 @luxas @andrewsykim ",
